{"title":"Sceptre of Torment","url":"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/Sceptre_of_Torment","type":"markdown","data":"***Version [0.31](/0.31 \"0.31\")**: This article **may not be** up to date for the [latest stable release](/0.32 \"0.32\") of Crawl.*\n\n|   |                                                                                                                                                                                         |\n| - | --------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |\n|   | An accursed golden sceptre, created by some unknown hellish power. When used in combat, it causes agonising pain in all those unfortunate enough to gaze upon it, save for the wielder. |\n\n[![Sceptre of torment.png](/images/3/3b/Sceptre_of_torment.png)](/File:Sceptre_of_torment.png) ***the +7 sceptre of Torment***\n\n+7 [eveningstar](/Eveningstar \"Eveningstar\")\n\n[Pain brand](/Pain_brand \"Pain brand\")  \nCasts [Symbol of Torment](/Symbol_of_Torment \"Symbol of Torment\") on 20% of successful attacks - the wielder is immune to these torments  \n[Evil](/Evil \"Evil\")\n\n## Desirability\n\nThe **sceptre of Torment**[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1) is an excellent weapon for those invested in [Necromancy](/Necromancy \"Necromancy\") that can take full advantage of the [pain brand](/Pain_brand \"Pain brand\"). Even with no Necromancy skill, a +7 eveningstar is still a respectable one-handed weapon for a [Maces & Flails](/Maces_%26_Flails \"Maces & Flails\") user. Its auto-torment effect is very useful in a standard 3-rune game, but becomes significantly less helpful in late-game areas where most monsters are immune to torment like the [Tomb](/Tomb \"Tomb\"), the [Hells](/Hells \"Hells\"), the [Abyss](/Abyss \"Abyss\"), and [Pandemonium](/Pandemonium \"Pandemonium\").\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [art-data.txt:311](https://github.com/crawl/crawl/blob/0.31.0/crawl-ref/source/art-data.txt#L311) (0.31.0)\n\n## History\n\n- Prior to [0.23](/0.23 \"0.23\"), the sceptre of Torment had a [staff](/Staff \"Staff\") as its base type, did not have the [pain](/Pain \"Pain\") brand, triggered torment on 50% of its attacks, and did not protect the wielder from its torment.\n- Prior to [0.20](/0.20 \"0.20\"), the sceptre of Torment also had a very small chance of activating each turn when you weren't attacking with it.\n- Prior to [0.17](/0.17 \"0.17\"), the sceptre of Torment had a [mace](/Mace \"Mace\") as its base type.\n- Prior to [0.15](/0.15 \"0.15\"), the Sceptre of Torment was a +7, +6 weapon.\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Sceptre of Torment - CrawlWiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Sceptre_of_Torment\",\"wgTitle\":\"Sceptre of Torment\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":80808,\"wgRevisionId\":80808,\"wgArticleId\":4384,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"0.31 articles\",\"Unrands\",\"Maces \\u0026 Flails\",\"Evil\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"July\",\"August\",\"September\",\"October\",\"November\",\"December\"],\"wgMonthNamesShort\":[\"\",\"Jan\",\"Feb\",\"Mar\",\"Apr\",\"May\",\"Jun\",\"Jul\",\"Aug\",\"Sep\",\"Oct\",\"Nov\",\"Dec\"],\"wgRelevantPageName\":\"Sceptre_of_Tor