.0\"/>\n<link rel=\"ExportRDF\" type=\"application/rdf+xml\" title=\"Sceptre of Torment\" href=\"/index.php?title=Special:ExportRDF/Sceptre_of_Torment&amp;xmlmime=rdf\"/>\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\"/>\n<link rel=\"search\" type=\"application/opensearchdescription+xml\" href=\"/opensearch_desc.php\" title=\"CrawlWiki (en)\"/>\n<link rel=\"EditURI\" type=\"application/rsd+xml\" href=\"http://crawl.chaosforge.org/api.php?action=rsd\"/>\n<!--[if lt IE 9]><script src=\"/resources/lib/html5shiv/html5shiv.min.js?40bd4\"></script><![endif]-->\n</head>\n<body class=\"mediawiki ltr sitedir-ltr mw-hide-empty-elt ns-0 ns-subject page-Sceptre_of_Torment rootpage-Sceptre_of_Torment skin-vector action-view\">\t\t<div id=\"mw-page-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"mw-head-base\" class=\"noprint\"></div>\n\t\t<div id=\"content\" class=\"mw-body\" role=\"main\">\n\t\t<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n\t\twindow.google_analytics_uacct = \"UA-3380984-8\";\n</script>\n<div class=\"adsense\">\n\t\t<script type=\"text/javascript\"><!--\n\t\tgoogle_ad_client = \"ca-pub-7088061744296615\";\n\t\t/* CrawlWiki skyscraper */\n\t\tgoogle_ad_slot = \"8196155564\";\n\t\tgoogle_ad_width = 160;\n\t\tgoogle_ad_height = 600;\n-->\n</script>\n<script type=\"text/javascript\"\nsrc=\"http://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/show_ads.js\">\n</script>\n</div>\n\n\t\t\t<a id=\"top\"></a>\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"mw-indicators mw-body-content\">\n</div>\n\t\t\t<h1 id=\"firstHeading\" class=\"firstHeading\" lang=\"en\">Sceptre of Torment</h1>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"bodyContent\" class=\"mw-body-content\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"siteSub\" class=\"noprint\">From CrawlWiki</div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"contentSub\"></div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"jump-to-nav\" class=\"mw-jump\">\n\t\t\t\t\tJump to:\t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#mw-head\">navigation</a>, \t\t\t\t\t<a href=\"#p-search\">search</a>\n\t\t\t\t</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\" class=\"mw-content-ltr\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div style=\"border: 1px solid #33FF66; background-color: #e0fae0; border-left: 15px solid #33FF66; margin-bottom: 20px; width: 100%; padding: 4px 10px; line-height: 1.1em; width: auto;\"><i><b>Version <a href=\"/0.31\" title=\"0.31\">0.31</a></b>: This article <b>may not be</b> up to date for the <a href=\"/0.32\" title=\"0.32\">latest stable release</a> of Crawl.</i></div>\n<table style=\"background:#f5faff; border:1px solid #cedff2; width:auto; margin: 0px 5%; margin-bottom:1.25em; font-style:italic; text-align:left; color:#000; padding:1.5em 1em;\">\n\n<tr>\n<td>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width: 100%;\"> An accursed golden sceptre, created by some unknown hellish power. When used in combat, it causes agonising pain in all those unfortunate enough to gaze upon it, save for the wielder.\n</td></tr></table>\n<p><a href=\"/File:Sceptre_of_torment.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Sceptre of torment.png\" src=\"/images/3/3b/Sceptre_of_torment.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\" /></a> <i><b>the +7 sceptre of Torment</b></i>\n</p><p>+7 <a href=\"/Eveningstar\" title=\"Eveningstar\">eveningstar</a>\n</p><p><a href=\"/Pain_brand\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pain brand\">Pain brand</a><br />\nCasts <a href=\"/Symbol_of_Torment\" title=\"Symbol of Torment\">Symbol of Torment</a> on 20% of successful attacks - the wielder is immune to these torments<br />\n<a href=\"/Evil\" title=\"Evil\">Evil</a>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Desirability\">Desirability</span></h2>\n<p>The <b>sceptre of Torment</b><sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> is an excellent weapon for those invested in <a href=\"/Necromancy\" title=\"Necromancy\">Necromancy</a> that can take full advantage of the <a href=\"/Pain_brand\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Pain brand\">pain brand</a>. Even with no Necromancy skill, a +7 eveningstar is still a respectable one-handed weapon for a <a href=\"/Maces_%26_Flails\" title=\"Maces &amp; Flails\">Maces &amp; Flails</a> user. Its auto-torment effect is very useful in a standard 3-rune game, but becomes significantly less helpful in late-game areas where most monsters are immune to torment like the <a href=\"/Tomb\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tomb\">Tomb</a>, the <a href=\"/Hells\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hells\">Hells</a>, the <a href=\"/Abyss\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Abyss\">Abyss</a>, and <a href=\"/Pandemonium\" title=\"Pandemonium\">Pandemonium</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/crawl/crawl/blob/0.31.0/crawl-ref/source/art-data.txt#L311\">art-data.txt:311</a> (0.31.0)</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span></h2>\n<ul><li>Prior to <a href=\"/0.23\" title=\"0.23\">0.23</a>, the sceptre of Torment had a <a href=\"/Staff\" title=\"Staff\">staff</a> as its base type, did not have the <a href=\"/Pain\" title=\"Pain\">pain</a> brand, triggered torment on 50% of its attacks, and did not protect the wielder from its torment.</li>\n<li>Prior to <a href=\"/0.20\" title=\"0.20\">0.20</a>, the sceptre of Torment also had a very small chance of activating each turn when you weren't attacking with it.</li>\n<li>Prior to <a href=\"/0.17\" title=\"0.17\">0.17</a>, the sceptre of Torment had a <a href=\"/Mace\" title=\"Mace\">mace</a> as its base type.</li>\n<li>Prior to <a href=\"/0.15\" title=\"0.15\">0.15</a>, the Sceptre of Torment was a +7, +6 weapon.</li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240916093301\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\n[SMW] In‐text annotation parser time: 0 seconds\nCPU time usage: 0.052 secon